==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turbidly
<hw>Tur"bid*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a
turbid manner; with muddiness or confusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Proudly; haughtily.</def> <mark>[A Latinism.
R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One of great merit <qex>turbidly</qex> resents them.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turbidness</ent>⟦br⟧
